we misread something.

85
00:05:06,730 --> 00:05:08,770
I said I've had enough.

86
00:05:08,770 --> 00:05:13,540
But what if we try re-reading it? 
We might discover something new!

87
00:05:14,100 --> 00:05:16,500
I'm going to give it a shot. Let's keep trying!

88
00:05:16,500 --> 00:05:18,500
I told you, I've had enough!

89
00:05:34,590 --> 00:05:35,720
Brother...

90
00:05:37,720 --> 00:05:39,150
Is something the matter?

91
00:05:47,050 --> 00:05:50,530
I'm sorry. I don't even 
want to look at it anymore.

92
00:05:51,240 --> 00:05:52,450
Brother...

93
00:06:01,650 --> 00:06:03,710
So, that's it, then?

94
00:06:05,960 --> 00:06:08,910
You won't regret 
having given up here?

95
00:06:13,030 --> 00:06:17,980
Is what you've been searching for something you would abandon this easily?

96
00:06:18,230 --> 00:06:21,690
Stop going on when you 
don't even know the half of it.

97
00:06:24,680 --> 00:06:29,640
I know. I know that you guys are seeking the Philosopher's Stone

98
00:06:29,640 --> 00:06:33,270
and that it is made by 
sacrificing living people.

99
00:06:35,470 --> 00:06:38,460
I knew it was rude, 
but I allowed myself to listen in.

100
00:06:40,090 --> 00:06:42,130
If you've listened in, 
then you must know

101
00:06:42,130 --> 00:06:45,550
that it won't do any good to investigate any further. Just leave us alone!

102
00:06:48,790 --> 00:06:50,300
You really are a child, huh?

103
00:06:52,030 --> 00:06:55,390
You're scared, right? 
That the answers might disappear?

104
00:06:56,960 --> 00:07:00,380
You don't want to acknowledge that everything you've gone through this far

105
00:07:00,380 --> 00:07:01,520
might be in vain, right?

106
00:07:03,720 --> 00:07:05,000
Am I wrong?

107
00:07:15,960 --> 00:07:18,790
Isn't it okay if it doesn't 
mean anything?

108
00:07:22,570 --> 00:07:27,300
Verifying whether or not this means anything is worth something, if you ask me.

109
00:07:27,740 --> 00:07:31,800
What you're seeking isn't 
anything all that simple, right?

110
00:07:32,810 --> 00:07:36,180
Why don't you keep trying 
a little longer, Edward-san?

111
00:07:48,010 --> 00:07:49,690
You're right...

112
00:07:49,930 --> 00:07:51,950
It's not as though the answers are going to change

113
00:07:51,950 --> 00:07:53,700
just because I chuck it 
all along the way.

114
00:07:54,500 --> 00:07:55,700
Brother!

115
00:07:56,520 --> 00:08:00,070
We've come this far! 
How can we end it all halfway?!

116
00:08:00,070 --> 00:08:01,710
We're going to 
see it to the end!

117
00:08:02,430 --> 00:08:03,680
Let's do it, Al!

118
00:08:03,680 --> 00:08:04,430
Mm-hmm!

119
00:08:08,920 --> 00:08:12,740
Marcoh-san's research is sound in theory.

120
00:08:12,740 --> 00:08:16,370
However, it still didn't result in a perfect Philosopher's Stone.

121
00:08:16,370 --> 00:08:18,430
There still might be other possibilities.

122
00:08:18,430 --> 00:08:23,830
Yeah. I'm going to verify the truth of Marcoh-san's theory with my own eyes.

123
00:08:24,630 --> 00:08:25,940
Truth?

124
00:08:30,110 --> 00:08:33,450
The genuine truth behind truths...

125
00:08:34,300 --> 00:08:37,090
Behind... truths...

126
00:08:38,380 --> 00:08:40,950
That's it! There's something else!

127
00:08:43,220 --> 00:08:44,920
According to this data,

128
00:08:44,920 --> 00:08:48,960
a considerably large facility would be needed to create a Philosopher's Stone.

129
00:08:49,310 --> 00:08:53,720
There are currently four alchemy laboratories under the military.

130
00:08:53,720 --> 00:08:59,220
Among those, Doctor Marcoh was assigned to the 3rd Laboratory.

131
00:08:59,220 --> 00:09:02,630
I went around to all of the laboratories in the city,

132
00:09:02,630 --> 00:09:05,900
and there wasn't any research 
all that remarkable going on there.

133
00:09:05,900 --> 00:09:07,810
Huh? What's this?

134
00:09:08,270 --> 00:09:11,740
Ah, in the past, 
that was the 5th laboratory,

135
00:09:11,740 --> 00:09:13,820
but it was closed down, 
and is deserted now.

136
00:09:14,530 --> 00:09:17,510
There's a risk of it collapsing, so it was made off-limits.

137
00:09:18,070 --> 00:09:18,820
It's there!

138
00:09:20,070 --> 00:09:20,830
Look.

139
00:09:21,820 --> 00:09:23,410
There's a prison next to it.

140
00:09:23,690 --> 00:09:26,120
Central 2nd Prison.

141
00:09:26,120 --> 00:09:27,660
What about it?

142
00:09:27,660 --> 00:09:30,540
With people being the ingredient for a Philosopher's Stone,

143
00:09:30,540 --> 00:09:34,420
what if they did their research there because it was the easiest place to procure them?

144
00:09:35,420 --> 00:09:37,180
You don't mean, they used prisoners?

145
00:09:37,180 --> 00:09:38,180
Yeah.

146
00:09:38,580 --> 00:09:40,200
If they didn't execute 
condemned criminals

147
00:09:40,200 --> 00:09:43,590
and instead used them as live materials, that would explain it.

148
00:09:43,590 --> 00:09:44,890
Who's in charge of 
the laboratories?

149
00:09:47,020 --> 00:09:49,910
That would have been 
Brig. Gen. Basque Grand.

150
00:09:49,910 --> 00:09:52,530
And he was killed by Scar 
some time ago.

151
00:09:55,950 --> 00:09:57,530
Brother...

152
00:09:57,530 --> 00:09:58,810
We've got no choice.

153
00:09:59,430 --> 00:10:01,230
How about we check things out directly?

154
00:10:01,230 --> 00:10:01,790
Mm-hmm.

155
00:10:01,790 --> 00:10:03,240
J-Just a moment!

156
00:10:03,990 --> 00:10:06,160
From here on, 
this is grown-ups' work.

157
00:10:06,160 --> 00:10:08,750
Besides, Scar is still after you.

158
00:10:08,750 --> 00:10:11,050
It's too dangerous for you 
to go walking around outside.

159
00:10:11,050 --> 00:10:12,750
Yeah, but still...

160
00:10:12,980 --> 00:10:17,720
We will investigate the 5th Laboratory. You wait here, please.

161
00:10:17,720 --> 00:10:20,010
If we learn anything, 
we will report it to you.

162
00:10:21,160 --> 00:10:22,430
If you please...

163
00:10:24,560 --> 00:10:25,520
Brother...

164
00:10:31,400 --> 00:10:33,980
So be it. Okay, it's up to you.

165
00:10:35,130 --> 00:10:36,950
We'll ask you to handle it.

166
00:10:36,950 --> 00:10:38,980
Right! Leave it to us!

167
