Lt. Colonel Hughes,

168
00:11:13,790 --> 00:11:18,860
I'm finished writing down the 
court record for case number 3263.

169
00:11:19,090 --> 00:11:22,680
Oh, is that right? 
Sorry, hang on a minute.

170
00:11:23,590 --> 00:11:27,240
Well, let's have you continue on with case number 9572, if you would.

171
00:11:28,040 --> 00:11:31,160
They're going to use it in a trial tomorrow, so put a rush on it.

172
00:11:32,380 --> 00:11:33,420
Okay...

173
00:11:33,420 --> 00:11:35,280
What's the matter?! Are you tired?!

174
00:11:35,280 --> 00:11:36,750
No, not particularly!

175
00:11:38,130 --> 00:11:41,600
Look here! This one is 
a special swimsuit version!

176
00:11:41,600 --> 00:11:44,740
What do you think? 
She's so cute, it just melts your heart!

177
00:11:44,740 --> 00:11:48,080
Just looking at this, the fatigue just flies away, doesn't it?

178
00:11:48,080 --> 00:11:50,480
How about it? Hm? Hm?

179
00:11:52,580 --> 00:11:53,380
Yes...

180
00:11:53,380 --> 00:11:55,130
It does, doesn't it?

181
00:11:54,310 --> 00:11:56,480
Um, Lt. Colonel...

182
00:11:55,130 --> 00:11:58,740
My daughter is such a little healer.

183
00:11:56,480 --> 00:11:58,740
Lt. Colonel! What is the problem there?!

184
00:11:59,800 --> 00:12:02,450
So, did you find Scar's body?

185
00:12:02,450 --> 00:12:03,950
Not yet, huh?

186
00:12:03,950 --> 00:12:07,910
All right. As for the matter of us sending security to the library,

187
00:12:07,910 --> 00:12:09,420
hurry and take care of that for me.

188
00:12:11,590 --> 00:12:14,860
Oh, I've been introduced to quite a find here.

189
00:12:14,860 --> 00:12:16,590
I owe one to Ed for her.

190
00:12:35,810 --> 00:12:37,550
Tripwire alarms?

191
00:12:37,550 --> 00:12:41,440
For a building that isn't being used, the security sure is tight, huh?

192
00:12:41,440 --> 00:12:42,820
This is getting more 
and more suspicious.

193
00:12:43,050 --> 00:12:44,870
All right, let's go around back.

194
00:12:52,160 --> 00:12:53,290
Al...

195
00:12:54,400 --> 00:12:56,380
Ups-a-daisy!

196
00:13:00,030 --> 00:13:02,650
I hate to say it, 
but it's times like this

197
00:13:02,650 --> 00:13:05,770
that I'm glad I don't have my flesh-and-blood arm and leg.

198
00:13:06,550 --> 00:13:07,500
Same here.

199
00:13:14,980 --> 00:13:17,130
This entrance is locked up tight, too, huh?

200
00:13:17,710 --> 00:13:19,060
Brother, over there...

201
00:13:26,150 --> 00:13:28,370
Looks like it goes 
all the way inside.

202
00:13:28,370 --> 00:13:29,910
Al, you wait here.

203
00:13:29,910 --> 00:13:31,580
Will you be all right 
by yourself?

204
00:13:31,910 --> 00:13:36,080
All right or not, your huge size won't fit through here, right?

205
00:13:36,080 --> 00:13:38,350
Okay, I'll be back in a bit.

206
00:13:39,300 --> 00:13:42,090
I'm not this big 
because I wanted to be!

207
00:13:44,090 --> 00:13:45,960
This is Lt. Maria Ross.

208
00:13:45,960 --> 00:13:48,090
Major Armstrong, please.

209
00:13:50,080 --> 00:13:51,360
What is it, Lieutenant?

210
00:13:51,360 --> 00:13:53,830
Major, I need to talk to you 
about something.

211
00:14:03,690 --> 00:14:04,150
Hey!

212
00:14:04,690 --> 00:14:07,340
Contact the Command Center at once, 
and call in reinforcements!

213
00:14:07,340 --> 00:14:08,110
Yes, sir!

214
00:14:16,280 --> 00:14:18,710
I have no business with you.

215
00:14:18,990 --> 00:14:21,290
Where is Fullmetal?!

216
00:14:34,270 --> 00:14:36,450
Two of you stay here! 
We're going up another stairway!

217
00:14:36,450 --> 00:14:38,420
He's going up to Edward-san's room!

218
00:15:14,810 --> 00:15:17,730
So Fullmetal knew about this too?

219
00:15:28,140 --> 00:15:29,600
Don't move, Scar!

220
00:15:37,210 --> 00:15:38,520
Lieutenant!

221
00:15:39,360 --> 00:15:40,950
Where are Edward-san 
and his brother?

222
00:15:40,950 --> 00:15:42,210
Please look at this.

223
00:15:46,040 --> 00:15:47,680
Those boys...

224
00:15:50,920 --> 00:15:52,010
The town of Liore...

225
00:15:52,620 --> 00:15:55,120
has been dealt with 
all neat and tidy.

226
00:15:55,120 --> 00:15:58,220
There's no longer anyone there who knows too much.

227
00:15:58,220 --> 00:16:00,850
You don't say. Nice work, Envy.

228
00:16:01,110 --> 00:16:03,520
Things are going well here too.

229
00:16:03,520 --> 00:16:07,340
The Fullmetal pipsqueak has caught wind of the laboratory, hasn't he?

230
00:16:07,340 --> 00:16:11,740
Shouldn't we dispose of him 
before it gets out to the military?

231
00:16:11,740 --> 00:16:13,820
If we're going to kill him, 
let me do it!

232
00:16:14,200 --> 00:16:18,700
Hold on. That boy might just grant us what we want.

233
00:16:19,000 --> 00:16:22,440
If we're going to kill him, it won't be too late to do so after that, will it?

234
00:16:22,440 --> 00:16:26,760
Well, it's fine with me as long as it doesn't throw a wrench in the works.

235
00:16:26,760 --> 00:16:30,920
Although, it seems doubtful that 
he would ever arrive there safely.

236
00:16:31,180 --> 00:16:36,300
I told them not to lay a hand on those two, but it is concerning.

237
00:16:36,590 --> 00:16:38,260
They <i>are</i> idiots, after all.

238
00:16:38,260 --> 00:16:41,100
If it looks to be too troublesome, dispose of the whole lot of them.

239
00:16:41,100 --> 00:16:42,530
I know.

240
00:16:44,060 --> 00:16:47,270
Damn, this is narrower than I thought.

241
00:16:47,270 --> 00:16:51,950
Damn it all, if I were normal-sized, 
I wouldn't have gotten through here.

242
00:16:51,950 --> 00:16:54,430
It's a good thing I'm so little.

243
00:16:55,390 --> 00:16:58,280
Augh! No, it's not!

244
00:17:07,480 --> 00:17:09,290
The lights are on...

245
00:17:10,150 --> 00:17:13,300
So they're not currently using it, huh?

246
00:17:13,300 --> 00:17:14,300
Bingo!

247
00:17:23,240 --> 00:17:24,740
Wh-What the?!

248
00:17:42,650 --> 00:17:47,790
For them to go this far, they must really not want anyone getting close.

249
00:17:47,790 --> 00:17:51,380
Sounds interesting! 
I'll take them on!

250
00:18:21,920 --> 00:18:26,410
Hey! Aren't we under orders not to lay a hand on them?

251
00:18:26,410 --> 00:18:32,420
I don't care about that. 
I can't rest until I've carved them up!

252
00:18:32,420 --> 00:18:35,920
